Detailed Description

Class that can be used to asynchronously perform a Gamaray refresh request.

Member Function Documentation

- (void) cancel  

Cancels performing the request.

- (void) didParseDimension: (ARDimension *)  aDimension  

Callback for the dimension parsing.

Parameters:
aDimension The dimension that was parsed, or nil if parsing failed.
- (id) initWithURL: (NSURL *)  url
spatialState: (ARSpatialState *)  spatialState
type: (ARDimensionRequestType)  type 

Initializes the receiver with the given values.

Parameters:
url The URL to which the request will be sent, must be non-nil. Supported URL schemes are http, gamaray and file.
spatialState The current spatial state of the device that will be sent to the server, must be non-nil.
type The type of request that will be sent to the server.
Returns:
The receiver.
- (NSURLRequest *) prepareRequest  

Creates and returns a NSURLRequest using the current values of the receiver.

- (void) start  

Starts performing the request, if it hasn't already started. This method returns immediately. The delegate will be notified when the request is done.

- (NSString *) uniqueIdentifier  

Returns a unique identifier suitable for a dimension request. In practice, returns the identifier of the device.

Property Documentation

- (id< ARDimensionRequestDelegate >) delegate [read, write, assign]

The delegate of the receiver that will be notified when the request finishes or fails.

- (CGSize) screenSize [read, write, assign]

The available room for overlays. Defaults to CGSizeZero, in which case no screen size will be provided to the server.

- (NSString *) source [read, write, retain]

The source of the request. Defaults to nil, in which case the string NULL will be sent to the server.

- (ARSpatialState *) spatialState [read, retain]

The current spatial state of the device, as provided to the initializer of this class.

- (ARDimensionRequestType) type [read, assign]

The type of refresh request, as provided to the initializer of this class.

- (NSURL *) url [read, retain]

The URL to which the request will be sent, as provided to the initializer of this class.
